6D. Greedy Signal Optimization Rules [ADDED]
Applied per intersection per time period.

  green_time(road_i) = (flow_i / total_flow_at_intersection) * cycle_time

  Emergency override:
    if emergency_vehicle_detected = True:
      set green_time = PreemptionHoldTime for approaching road
      set red_time   = PreemptionHoldTime for all other roads
      resume normal cycle after RecoveryCycleTime seconds

  Greedy is optimal when:
    - Flows are stable and predictable (normal daily patterns)
    - Only one intersection is being optimized at a time

  Greedy is suboptimal when:
    - Multiple adjacent intersections interact (requires global coordination)
    - Unexpected events occur (accidents, protests) not reflected in flow data
--------------------------------------------------------


