SECTION 9 — SCENARIO DEFINITIONS [ADDED]
Reason: The project requires demonstrating performance under
different scenarios. These are predefined test cases that
cover all required algorithm behaviors.
================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------
SCENARIO A — Standard Route Planning (Dijkstra)
Tests time-dependent weight changes across all four periods.
--------------------------------------------------------

Query 1:  From=4  (New Cairo)         To=3  (Downtown Cairo)   Period=MorningPeak
Query 2:  From=4  (New Cairo)         To=3  (Downtown Cairo)   Period=Night
Query 3:  From=7  (6th October City)  To=2  (Nasr City)        Period=EveningPeak
Query 4:  From=12 (Helwan)            To=13 (New Admin Capital) Period=Afternoon
Query 5:  From=11 (Shubra)            To=15 (Sheikh Zayed)     Period=MorningPeak

Expected behavior: Travel times in MorningPeak and EveningPeak
should be significantly higher than Afternoon and Night on
congested roads (congestion ratio >= 0.75).

--------------------------------------------------------
SCENARIO B — Emergency Vehicle Routing (A*)
Tests hospital reachability and response time from each district.
--------------------------------------------------------

Query 1:  From=7   (6th October City)  To=F9  (Qasr El Aini Hospital)
Query 2:  From=13  (New Admin Capital) To=F9  (Qasr El Aini Hospital)
Query 3:  From=12  (Helwan)            To=F10 (Maadi Military Hospital)
Query 4:  From=4   (New Cairo)         To=F9  (Qasr El Aini Hospital)
Query 5:  From=7   (6th October City)  To=F10 (Maadi Military Hospital)

All queries run at Period=MorningPeak (worst-case response time).
Compare A* result with Dijkstra result to demonstrate speed advantage.

--------------------------------------------------------
SCENARIO C — Road Closure / Alternate Route (Dijkstra)
Tests system behavior when a major road is blocked.
--------------------------------------------------------

Block road: 3-5 (Downtown to Heliopolis) — simulates accident
Query: From=2 (Nasr City) To=8 (Giza), Period=MorningPeak
Expected: System must reroute through alternate nodes.
Compare travel time before and after closure.

Block road: 13-4 (New Admin Capital to New Cairo) — simulates closure
Query: From=13 To=3 (Downtown Cairo), Period=Afternoon

--------------------------------------------------------
SCENARIO D — MST Infrastructure Design
Tests Kruskal's with and without potential new roads.
--------------------------------------------------------

Run 1: MST using existing roads only
Run 2: MST using existing + potential new roads
Compare: Total distance, construction cost, critical nodes covered.

Constraint check: Verify F9, F10, F1, F2, and node 13 are
all included in the final spanning tree.

--------------------------------------------------------
SCENARIO E — Traffic Signal Optimization (Greedy)
Tests signal timing allocation at peak vs. off-peak hours.
--------------------------------------------------------

Intersection: I1 (Tahrir Square) — highest traffic volume
Period 1: MorningPeak — allocate green time by flow proportion
Period 2: Night       — reallocate green time by night flow

Emergency test: Trigger preemption at I1 during MorningPeak.
Show: time saved, recovery cycle, impact on other roads.

Suboptimal case: I1 and I4 adjacent — Greedy optimizes each
independently but produces suboptimal combined throughput.
Compare against brute-force optimal to quantify the gap.

--------------------------------------------------------
SCENARIO F — DP Scheduling
Tests bus allocation across time slots.
--------------------------------------------------------

Input:  Fleet availability per slot (Section 8C)
        Demand per OD pair (Section 7C)
        Route coverage (Section 7B)

Objective: Maximize total passengers served per day
Constraint: Total buses deployed per slot <= available fleet

Show DP table construction and optimal allocation decision.
Compare optimized schedule against current assignment.

--------------------------------------------------------
SCENARIO G — DP Maintenance (Knapsack)
Tests road prioritization under budget constraint.
--------------------------------------------------------

Budget: 200 Million EGP (Section 5)
Input:  All 34 existing roads with cost and priority (Section 5)

Objective: Maximize total priority score of maintained roads
Constraint: Total cost <= 200 Million EGP

Critical constraint: Roads with priority=5 (hospital access,
Ramses Station) must be included regardless of cost.

Show selected roads, total cost, total priority score, and
which high-priority roads were excluded due to budget limits.


